Awesome, cozy, inviting little brewery pub.  Nice selection of beer AND they have a great craft brewed coffee.  Highly suggested!

Enjoyed the great service and quality craft on tap! The Wicked Felina and Small Batch: 2 Hop IPA were so refreshing on a hot El Paso evening. Will definitely return to continue the tour of their beer menu!

Very excited to see these breweries in our area doing well. This brewery was designed well great flow to the establishment tasty beer loved me the Thunderbird and a friendly staff. This us how breweries should be top to bottom
Stopped by today for the first time.  I really liked the El Matador beer.  I'll be adding it to my list of places that I need to visit at least one a month.

Nice place.
Loved this place from the first taste. Prices are reasonable.
Solid food and drinks. Few bar games to enjoy as well.

Beer was good. Food AWFUL, Atmosphere terrible. Staff inattentive.  We seek out local breweries where ever we go. The online pics looked good so we gave this a try. The only thing good I can say is that they had a good variety of tasty …

Happy that local breweries are succeeding, especially El Paso Brewing. They have a variety of good beer and food on site and the best service around. We visited for the drinks/food and return for the awesome crew making it happen everyday. Thanks again guys!!!
Server was awesome!! Food was great. I had a chicken and cactus quesadilla. Beer was decent. Had a good Scottish ale and ipa. No cream ales here though. Worth a stop.
Fun, clean and great beer

I went here on a random week night with a few friends and was pleasantly surprised.  The beer here is very decent, and the location itself is very inviting.  Parking is somewhat limited and is available only on the street.  Also, they do …

Went to El Paso Brewing on a whim since I normally don't drink beer. After going I liked the vibe of the place and can honestly say I enjoyed the beer. The service was great and friendly. When I go back into town I'll be passing by again.
Ruben is the man! Im here from San Jose, CA to taste the beer.. Ruben provided wonderful service and also a tour of the beer making.. Stop by and take a look! N taste!
A nice little quick place to get a beer 🍻

So proud to start seeing more brewery options open up in my beautiful and extremely underrated city. The server, bartender, and chef were all in one and it was all great! Keep up the great work, looking forward to trying any and all new brews to come!
Nice, relaxing Sunday spot.  Good games, friendly staff and if you are an IPA fan, I highly recommend the Dark Felina Black IPA and the Wicked Felina.
Really good atmosphere and good beer.
Mmm mmm good
Very nice place. Lost of games to play. Great atmosphere. Satisfying customer service. Besides the beer can order food, coffee, tea. Great for groups and hanging out. Will be going back again.
Awesome layout, light pumpkin pie, finger foods and bad arse brews..

Great place to have a beer with a small group of friends. Any bigger than 20 folks find some place else. They don't have the staff to accommodate large groups. With that said it's still a cool place to hang out. Great beer

Not only was the beer fantastic and the atmosphere welcoming, the staff was incredibly friendly and offered to give us a tour of the brewing area. I’ve been on a number of brewery tours before, but this was definitely the most personal and informative one I’ve ever been on.
Very cool place to hang. Good food good beer. Staff is very friendly. Definitely will go again

Very good place good bear l like that they have table games.
Food was nice but quite overpriced. Good beer.
Great local brewing. Gentle waiters. Delicious beers. Normal price.
Great vibe. Friendly. Board games! Good variety of eats, original beverages.

Very cool space that is open and inviting. Throw in friendly  staff and quaffable beers and you have the start of a good hangout.  I was particular impressed with a well balanced IPA which was hoppy enough to be identifiable as an IPA but …
Friendly staff, good variety of beers, and had good food to snack on.  I enjoyed the tour of the microbrewery.  Nice place to stop and have a beer on your way home from work.

Jonathan & Carlos,  Master brewers are always working hard to brew the BEST possible beer in town! Awesome place to have a beer and a little something to eat. Great beer....great food.... Good peeps! Check it out!

Two weeks after visiting the first time the bartender still remembered the beer I liked. Good beer too!

When this place first opened up, they had maybe 4 beers to pick from. Now the selection has grown quite a bit, ranging from all different types of brews. You'll definitely find a beer to quench your thirst. Personal favorites are the Pachuco pale ale (hoppy and floral) and the Whiptail dunkel (malty and smooth).

The brews are good. If you like beer you will definitely like this place.   You do have to order  at the bar so don't stand around waiting for a waitress.  Only reason I gave it 4 is because the beer should be served at a lower temperature
